 {"id":"bd-3fc.2","title":"Conformance harness with terminal emulator matrix","description":"Automated conformance testing across 5 terminal emulators (xterm-256color, screen-256color, kitty, alacritty, WezTerm). Each emulator tested via virtual PTY or container. Test matrix: widget_type x emulator x color_depth x unicode_support. Failure isolation: identify emulator-specific bugs. CI integration: matrix build in GitHub Actions. TRACING: span 'conformance.run' with fields: emulator, widget, color_depth, result. LOG: INFO per test result. METRICS: gauge conformance_pass_rate{emulator=...}.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:05:11.960548365Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:05:55.552497300Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ci","conformance","emulators","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3fc.2","depends_on_id":"bd-3fc","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3fc.2","depends_on_id":"bd-3fc.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-3fc.3","title":"Fuzz testing harness for ANSI parser and input handling","description":"cargo-fuzz targets: (1) ANSI parser: arbitrary bytes -> no panic, no UB, no infinite loop. (2) Input widget: arbitrary UTF-8 + control sequences -> no panic. (3) Layout engine: arbitrary constraint sets -> no panic, no negative dimensions. (4) Widget tree: arbitrary event sequences -> no panic. Continuous fuzzing in CI (oss-fuzz integration). TRACING: not needed in fuzzer itself. Crash artifacts stored with full tracing replay. METRICS: counter fuzz_iterations_total, counter fuzz_crashes_found_total.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:05:12.046592011Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:05:55.700569124Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ansi","fuzz","input","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3fc.3","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3fc.3","depends_on_id":"bd-3fc","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-3fc.4","title":"Performance regression gate with criterion benchmarks","description":"criterion benchmark suite: (1) Frame render time (p50/p95/p99/p999), (2) Layout computation time, (3) Diff strategy time, (4) Widget render time per type, (5) ANSI emit bytes/frame. CI gate: regression alert if p99 increases by >10% vs baseline. Baseline stored in tests/baseline.json. Flamegraph generated per benchmark. TRACING: benchmark mode captures spans for profiling. LOG: WARN for regression alert. METRICS: all performance metrics fed into slo.yaml validation.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:05:12.311613609Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:05:55.847581885Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["criterion","performance","regression","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3fc.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3fc","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3fc.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3fc.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:01Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
